config.text: HPMS Curve Classes

Summary:

Curve will be delivered as a polygon feature encompassing the entire travel area of the roadway. A new polygon will be started anytime the curve radius changes by more than 5% or if 1/10th of a mile has been reached.

Additional Info:

This product uses the LiDAR-based extracted attributes from our Edge of Travel dataset to ascertain the roadway curvature.

config.text:
Welcome to the KDOT Data Collection Hub!

Check out the content and links below for a detailed explanation of this project, the current status and more information about how you can access the data and imagery.
Project Status
Our Collection Status Dashboard provides a dynamic view of your state's imagery and LiDAR collection.
"Phase 0" Data Review

We want to ensure that we are providing your state with the highest quality extraction possible. DOT staff are encouraged to review and provide feedback on these extracted assets using our Data Review App.
Data Dictionary
The Data Dictionary provides a complete breakdown of the schema for our extracted assets. Both attributes and their corresponding values are defined for every extracted dataset.
Extraction Details

When extracting assets along your state's roadways, we do our utmost to adhere to the agreed upon data dictionary. However, there are always unexpected circumstances along the way which may fall outside of the norm. The Extraction Details log documents as many scenarios as we could find and provides our reasoning.
Project at-a-glance
Driving the Collection Area
For the RIVaL proof-of-concept (POC) demonstration, we drove along several roadways in Central Austin
All Routes
100%
Completed
Capture Imagery & LiDAR
A major part of the RIVaL project involves capturing high-resolution imagery and LIDaR at an interval of approximately every 5 meters for the entire collection area.
A Total of
15,624
Images Captured
Asset Extraction

Using the 100 megapixel, 360 degree imagery, paired with our HD LIDaR, we extracted the 4 assets required by the RIVaL POC: Inside Shoulders, Outside Shoulders, Maximum Speed Limit and Number of Lanes
A Total of
1,114
Assets Extracted
